      "content": "Spacing them out is a weak attempt to sidestep a biological problem. Those enzymes are persistent and can affect your system for longer than you think. If you're truly concerned about timing, try a high dose of Vitamin C tablets right before your juice, as that will temporarily overwhelm the absorption pathways. Most importantly, your primary focus should be on keeping your doctor informed, but in the meantime, just use a different drink.",
